----

On 8 September 2003, thanks to a super science waste management facility [[[bury-the-survivors-hub |gone bananas]]], 8 September 2002 recurs instead and the entire world is changed. For the better, if you ask the seven unlucky sods who originally died, and are now explosively alive. For the worse, if you ask the billions of ordinary people now in daily danger of being atomized, brainwashed, or transmogrified into gooey flesh-sculptures. It's almost enough to make you wonder if totalitarian shadow governments are worth it!

The staff of SCP Foundation Research and Containment Site-43 are all that stands between the survivors of the human race and total oblivion. There's a whole lot more standing between them, however, and it'll be an uphill battle to reconvene and plot out the salvation of their species... not only in this timeline, but across them all.

