//will you remember me//

//when everything changes;//
//the wolf pursuing,//
//and the way shut?//
//friends afield and//
//the foe in your head,//
//encased, entombed, with//
//dirt heaped above,//
//shrouded in darkness...//
//but you are the light.//
//when you find your feet//
//and friends,//
//and a second beacon bright,//
//and you ask yourself: do i hold the line?//
//can i carry alone this wait?//
//that endless weight//
//compressing you to dust,//
//your world ablaze//
//and heart a withered rag;//
//and you speak your peace//
//and supplant the faithless//
//to walk roads untravelled//
//to their terminus,//
//where nothing stays strange,//
//and weary feet fall//
//on spiral paths in dust...//

//will you remember me?//
[[/collapsible]]
